    "recap_headline": "Princeton University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "ROCK HILL, S.C. -\nPrinceton baseball started off their series against Winthrop with a strong 10-3 win.\nPrinceton's offense erupted in the fourth inning with a seven-run rally.\nWill Robbins\nstarted by doubling down the left field line, bringing home\nJake Kernodle\nwhile\nJake Koonin\nadvanced to third. Moments later, Koonin scored on an error by Winthrop.\nIsaac Lamson\nextended the lead with an RBI double, bringing\u00a0in Robbins and\nDylan Zdunek\nto make it 4-0.\nGrant Werdesheim\nfollowed with an RBI single that scored\nBrady Kaufman\n, and following another error, Lamson and Werdesheim made it to home, making it 7-0.\nThe Tigers added insurance late in the game. In the eighth inning,\nJake Koonin\ndelivered an RBI single to score Kernodle, and Robbins added another run with an RBI groundout that brought home Bennet Crerar. Princeton closed out their scoring in the ninth when\nTommy Googins\ndrove in Kaufman with a groundout to make it 10-3.\nWinthrop attempted to rally late with three runs across the sixth and eighth innings, but could not inch closer.\nPrinceton starter\nJames Beasley\nallowed just five hits and one run.\nJackson Baldrate\nfinished the game with a scoreless ninth to secure the win.\nPrinceton continues its series against Winthrop Wednesday. First pitch is set for 4 p.m."
